%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbout%20three-quarters%20of%20the%20work%20patterns%20we%20observed%20did%20not%20strictly%20conform%20to%20working%20stably%20during%20daytime%20hours%20throughout%20our%20working%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Wen-Jui%20Han%2C%20the%20sole%20author%20of%20the%20study%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20Silver%20School%20of%20Social%20Work%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20conducted%20by%20the%20journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Han%2C%20whose%20expertise%20lies%20in%20social%20welfare%20policy%20concerning%20children%20and%20families%2C%20emphasized%20the%20consequences%20of%20such%20work%20patterns%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20repercussions.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20with%20work%20patterns%20involving%20any%20degree%20of%20volatility%20and%20variability%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20fewer%20hours%20of%20sleep%20per%20day%2C%20lower%20sleep%20quality%2C%20lower%20physical%20and%20mental%20functions%2C%20and%20a%20higher%20likelihood%20of%20reporting%20poor%20health%20and%20depressive%20symptoms%20at%20age%2050%20than%20those%20with%20stable%20standard%20work%20schedules%2C%26quot%3B%20Han%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Dr%20Han%20explored%20how%20these%20associations%20were%20influenced%20by%20social%20factors%20such%20as%20race%20or%20ethnicity%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20challenges%20posed%20by%20modern%20work%20schedules%2C%20health%20experts%20suggest%20there%20are%20strategies%20individuals%20can%20employ%20to%20alleviate%20their%20negative%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20led%20by%20Dr%20Han%2C%20analyzed%20data%20from%20over%207%2C300%20young%20adults%20(ages%2014-22)%20followed%20over%20time.%20It%20found%20that%20those%20who%20switched%20from%20having%20stable%20work%20schedules%20(starting%20around%206%20am%20and%20ending%20by%206%20pm)%20to%20irregular%20or%20unpredictable%20schedules%20between%20ages%2022%20and%2049%20reported%20the%20worst%20health%20outcomes%20at%20age%2050.%20This%20negative%20impact%20was%20significant%2C%20comparable%20to%20having%20a%20lower-than-high%20school%20education.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20study%20suggests%20that%20even%20periods%20of%20unemployment%20were%20less%20detrimental%20to%20long-term%20health%20than%20consistently%20irregular%20work%20schedules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20revealed%20racial%20and%20gender%20differences.%20Black%20participants%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20assigned%20schedules%20linked%20to%20poorer%20health%20outcomes.%20Additionally%2C%20women%20reported%20lower%20sleep%20quality%20despite%20getting%20more%20total%20sleep%20hours.%20While%20the%20reasons%20for%20these%20disparities%20are%20unclear%2C%20the%20researchers%20suggest%20it%20might%20be%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bintersectionality%26quot%3B%20-%20the%20combined%20impact%20of%20race%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20job%20security%20on%20health.%20They%20point%20out%20that%20these%20findings%20highlight%20existing%20health%20inequalities%2C%20where%20those%20with%20fewer%20resources%20face%20a%20greater%20burden%20from%20unpredictable%20work%20schedules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20results%20aren't%20exactly%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20surprising%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20timely%20and%20alarming%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Xiaoxi%20Yao%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20health%20services%20research%20at%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%20in%20Minnesota.%20She%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20in%20higher%20socio-economic%20status%20might%20enjoy%20the%20flexibility%20of%20working%20from%20anywhere%20at%20any%20time%2C%20whereas%20people%20in%20the%20so-called%20vulnerable%20social%20positions%20might%20not%20have%20a%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Yao%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20often%20worried%20about%20these%20workers'%20wages%20and%20benefits%20but%20this%20study%20calls%20out%20that%20the%20non-standard%20work%20schedules%20and%20hours%20might%20inherently%20put%20workers%20at%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20study%20reveals%20a%20link%20between%20work%20patterns%20and%20health%20outcomes%2C%20experts%20caution%20it%20doesn't%20prove%20cause%20and%20effect.%20Several%20theories%20could%20explain%20the%20association%2C%20but%20further%20research%20is%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20person%20can%20have%20some%20risk%20factors%20that%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20both%20find%20a%20stable%20job%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20develop%20a%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Yao%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20difficult%20to%20use%20the%20current%20data%20to%20draw%20a%20firm%20conclusion%20that%20the%20work%20schedules%2Fhours%20caused%20the%20adverse%20health%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20switching%20jobs%20or%20schedules%20might%20not%20be%20an%20option%20for%20everyone%2C%20Dr%20Yao%20suggests%20there%20are%20other%20ways%20to%20manage%20the%20potential%20downsides%20of%20irregular%20work.%20These%20strategies%20include%20maintaining%20a%20healthy%20diet%2C%20exercising%20regularly%2C%20prioritizing%20relaxation%20techniques%2C%20and%20nurturing%20relationships%20with%20loved%20ones%2C%20Dr%20Yao%20suggests.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712234520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Ffmjta9io_working-generic_625x300_04_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Ferratic-work-hours-can-harm-your-health-decades-later-study-5374424%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Irregular%20work%20schedules%20may%20increase%20your%20risk%20of%20health%20problems%20later%20in%20life%2C%20a%20new%20study%20suggests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Ferratic-work-hours-can-harm-your-health-decades-later-study-5374424%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2