s%20of%20weaponry%2C%20ammunition%2C%20and%20manpower%2C%20experts%20and%20Western%20intelligence%20say.%20Jackie%20said%20Ukraine's%20troops%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efighting%20against%20Russia's%20invasion%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20used%20to%20fighting%20with%20less%20artillery%20than%20the%20Russians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Ukraine%20has%20still%20often%20been%20able%20to%20beat%20Russia%20because%20of%20better%20tactics%20and%20training%2C%20a%20view%20taken%20by%20most%20observers%20to%20explain%20how%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20able%20to%20stop%20Russia%20from%20taking%20over%20the%20country%20and%20even%20take%20back%20some%20territory%20from%20Russia%20in%20the%20east%20despite%20having%20a%20much%20smaller%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20shortages%20has%20been%20changing%20that%20dynamic%2C%20Jackie%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-troops-low-on-war-materiel-repel-large-russian-assault-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%20has%20still%20had%20some%20victories%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20its%20low%20supplies%2C%20but%20it%20is%20getting%20harder.%20Russia%20has%20been%20pushing%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJackie%20said%20that%20before%20the%20shortages%20really%20began%20to%20hit%20hard%2C%20Ukraine%20had%20often%20used%20its%20artillery%20to%20suppress%20Russia's%20own%20artillery%2C%20allowing%20what%20he%20called%20Ukraine's%20superior%20infantry%20to%20dominate%20Russia's%20while%20being%20targeted%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Russian%20general%20last%20year%20even%20acknowledged%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-generals-concerns-show-ukraine-bloodying-russia-in-key-fight-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%20was%20beating%20Russia%20in%20this%20type%20of%20fighting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20counter-battery%20combat%2C